{"nodes": [{"id": "docs_ard_genesis", "label": "GENESIS System", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Split into a Python Neuromorphic Physics Engine backend and a Vanilla-JS Observation Deck frontend, connected over a single WebSocket (ws://<host>:8085); earlier opcode/graph engines (turing_engine.py, genesis_engine.py, DynamicBrain) were deleted in favour of the genome-encoded SNN engine."}, {"id": "docs_ard_neuromorphic_engine", "label": "neuromorphic_engine.py", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The hot path: an SNN simulator compiled to machine code with Numba @njit(cache=True) for speed; holds the memory allocator, genome decoder, sensory encoder and world_tick_numba."}, {"id": "docs_ard_genesis_lab", "label": "genesis_lab.py", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Owns all global state (NumPy arrays), the deep-time sim_loop, reproduction/mutation, the Elite Ark, and the asyncio/websockets server."}, {"id": "docs_ard_books_of_genesis", "label": "books_of_genesis.py", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_ard_ram_substrate", "label": "The Universe (RAM Substrate)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.2", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Space is literal RAM: a 1D toroidal uint8 array of RAM_SIZE=65536 bytes (g_ram). Position is a byte address, movement is pointer arithmetic mod RAM_SIZE; food is byte 0x55, curriculum/Oracle text occupies printable ASCII 32-126."}, {"id": "docs_ard_global_heap", "label": "The Global Heap", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.3", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "No per-organism matrices: neurons, synapses and genomes for the whole universe live in flat global arrays and each organism mallocs contiguous blocks via malloc_block/free_block. Models the universe's total computational matter as one shared heap, so memory fragmentation is itself a spatial hazard."}, {"id": "docs_ard_genome_encoded_snn", "label": "Genome-Encoded SNN Organism", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.4", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A genome is a byte string parsed into three record types (receptor, neuron, synapse); every organism has a fixed I/O layer of N_INPUT=15 sensory + N_OUTPUT=14 motor neurons plus variable hidden neurons."}, {"id": "docs_ard_receptor_protein", "label": "Receptor Protein (RECEPTOR_MARKER 195)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.4", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A 10-byte DNA-encoded plasticity profile (A_PLUS, A_MINUS, TAU_P, TAU_M, V_REST, V_RESET, TAU_DEFAULT, SPIKE_RATE_MAX); up to MAX_RECEPTORS_PER_ORG=16 per organism."}, {"id": "docs_ard_hidden_neuron", "label": "Hidden Neuron (NEURON_MARKER 162)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.4", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A 5-byte record expressing a receptor id, a threshold and a leak time-constant."}, {"id": "docs_ard_synapse_gene", "label": "Synapse Gene (GENE_MARKER 161)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.4", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A 4-byte synapse record (src, dst, weight) where weight maps a raw byte to float(w)-128, i.e. -128..+127."}, {"id": "docs_ard_leaky_integrate_and_fire", "label": "Leaky Integrate-and-Fire Model", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.5", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "float32 voltage: leak v += (v_rest - v)/tau, fire when v >= threshold, reset to v_reset, refractory TAU_REF=1 step; input neurons fire stochastically proportional to sensed value x SPIKE_RATE_MAX."}, {"id": "docs_ard_stdp", "label": "STDP (Hebbian Plasticity)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.5", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "On a post-synaptic spike, pre-before-post potentiates (w += A_PLUS\u00b7e^(-\u0394t/TAU_P)) and pre-after-post depresses (w -= A_MINUS\u00b7e^(-\u0394t/TAU_M)); weights clamp to [W_MIN, W_MAX] = [-128, 127]."}, {"id": "docs_ard_baldwin_learning", "label": "Baldwin-style In-Lifetime Learning", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.5", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Lifetime STDP changes are held in the runtime weight array; behavioural adaptation acquired within a lifetime is not itself directly inherited (contrast with the Lamarckian 50/50 blend)."}, {"id": "docs_ard_lamarckian_consolidation", "label": "Lamarckian Consolidation", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.6 / \u00a71.5", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "At reproduction the birth path (neuromorphic_engine.py ~L498-521) re-walks the child's copied genome like decode_genome and overwrites each hidden/output synapse weight byte with a 50/50 blend of the parent's initial DNA weight and the weight the parent learned via STDP this lifetime (global_conn_weight, re-encoded +128), making acquired plasticity partially heritable. The 50/50 constants are hardcoded inline (a Rule 17 target for DNA-encoding). Corrects a stale earlier claim that learned weights were never written back."}, {"id": "docs_ard_observation_deck", "label": "Frontend Observation Deck", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Vanilla-JS frontend (public/) rendering the 65536-byte RAM as a folded 256x256 HTML5 canvas; includes KPI tiles, an extinction chart, a D3 Brain Analyzer that decompiles the Elite genome's synapses, an Oracle Terminal, and a Library of Genesis curriculum injector."}, {"id": "docs_ard_sensors_motors", "label": "Sensors (15) and Motors (14)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.6", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Inputs: energy reserve, bias, crowding, RAM byte under pointer, neighbours' vocal-cord bits, and the 8 bits of the Oracle broadcast (7-14). Outputs: jumps +/-1 and +/-10, consume, reproduce, and 8 vocal-cord bits (emitted ASCII character)."}, {"id": "docs_ard_thermodynamics_cpu_cycles", "label": "Thermodynamics = CPU Cycles", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Energy is execution cycles (ATP_MAX=1,000,000 ceiling) drained per action at honest raw-cycle counts (Rule 15/17): synapse transmission 1, neuron membrane update 1\u00d7n_neurons/step, activity-gated STDP update 1, movement 3, viscosity stall n_neurons; consume +1024. Neuron update was formerly discounted to 0.1\u00d7 (brain size ~10\u00d7 too cheap), so billing at true rate makes lean brains out-reproduce costly ones \u2014 Rule 7 efficiency selected emergently by thermodynamics, never a fitness metric. Costs are activity-gated to reward many sparsely-firing synapses (the 20 W paradigm, Rule 11)."}, {"id": "docs_ard_computational_viscosity", "label": "Computational Viscosity (Rule 13)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.2", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Local code density in a \u00b116-byte window sets a stall probability (up to 0.5) each tick; stalled steps burn maintenance energy but do no computation, penalising dense genomes and favouring sparse topologies."}, {"id": "docs_ard_conservation_of_compute", "label": "Conservation of Compute", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.3", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Per-tick LIF step budget is a global pool: steps = GLOBAL_CYCLE_POOL(3000)/population; mass replication dilutes everyone's compute, coupling population to a fixed energy budget."}, {"id": "docs_ard_cosmic_radiation", "label": "Cosmic Radiation (Entropy)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.4", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Two random bit-flips per tick applied inside living organisms' genomes (germline mutation) rather than the mostly-empty 5 MB arena where ~99% of flips previously landed in vacuum. Known limitation: phenotype is decoded once at spawn, so a flip alters offspring not the running brain \u2014 true in-lifetime somatic entropy is future work."}, {"id": "docs_ard_elite_ark", "label": "The Elite Ark (Rule 14)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.5", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "sim_loop continuously tracks the highest-age living genome; on total extinction the universe is reseeded (300 organisms) from mutated copies of that Elite, guaranteeing strictly ascending evolution. The Elite genome is checkpointed to Brain/Brain.npz."}, {"id": "docs_ard_reproduction_mutation", "label": "Reproduction & Mutation", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.6", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Reproduce pays genome_length\u00d7CYCLES_PER_BYTE_COPY then splits remaining energy 50/50 with the child; organism dies at energy<=0. mutate_dna applies insertion/deletion/gene-duplication (5% each) else point mutations at rate 1/genome_length; receptor-marker bytes 0-1 are protected so a lineage cannot lose all STDP in one flip."}, {"id": "docs_ard_oracle_uplink", "label": "Oracle Uplink & Curriculum", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "User can broadcast an 8-bit character (sensed on inputs 7-14), read back the Elite's vocal-cord output, and inject ASCII books as byte patterns into the substrate \u2014 a still-human-in-the-loop scaffold toward the Autotelic Imperative (Rule 9)."}, {"id": "docs_ard_autotelic_imperative", "label": "The Autotelic Imperative (Rule 9)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The long-term goal of a self-directed, self-teaching system that removes the human-in-the-loop curriculum scaffold."}, {"id": "docs_ard_mutate_dna", "label": "mutate_dna", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.6", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_ard_decode_genome", "label": "decode_genome", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.6", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_ard_world_tick_numba", "label": "world_tick_numba", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_ard_numba_njit", "label": "Numba @njit(cache=True)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Ahead-of-time cached JIT compilation to machine code, used to make the SNN hot path fast."}, {"id": "docs_ard_elite_iq", "label": "elite_iq Dashboard Metric", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a72.1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "elite_iq = age / footprint is observation-only and must never feed back into selection (Rule 5/9); efficiency must remain emergent from thermodynamics, not an imposed fitness metric."}], "edges": [{"source": "docs_ard_genesis", "target": "docs_ard_neuromorphic_engine", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_ard_genesis", "target": "docs_ard_genesis_lab", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_ard_genesis", "target": "docs_ard_books_of_genesis", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "Docs/ARD.md", "source_location": "\u00a71.1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_ard_genesis", "target": "docs_ard_observation_deck", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "sourc